          "date": "2013-08-26 14:20:51.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-136 build: add vmalloc option to allocate sbi->s_group_desc",
        "message": "LU-136 build: add vmalloc option to allocate sbi->s_group_desc\n\nLarge kmalloc() for the group descriptor buffer pointers can\nfail for large filesystems, which will cause the \"not enough\nmemory\" error while mounting. Fall back to vmalloc() if the\nkmalloc() failed, as was done for s_flex_groups.\n\nThis patch is being revived to perform large-lun, 32TB,\ntesting on b1_8.\n\nSigned-off-by: Yu Jian <yujian@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I09c4e51026825ec73fe30658bc062b277d2ff6e7\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <james.a.nunez@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
